| text = I find it ironic that the people of the Vilhon continue to poison their own farms, streams, and air for the sake of profit. The destruction caused by these people goes far beyond the borders of the Vilhon, but this is my home. I find my actions limited by my status of Grand Druid, and look forward to the time when I can find a suitable replacement. Then, I will finally be able to make a difference.
| source = Grand Druid [[Shinthala Deepcrest]]
}}
Based out of the isle of Ilighôn, the Emerald Enclave's heart was the House of Silvanus, or Oakenhall, built atop the mountain range at the center of the island. By the late 14{{th}} century DR, the Emerald Enclave had expanded its scope beyond the Vilhon Reach to the rest of Faerûn. To protect forests that would surely eventually face danger from encroaching civilization, it formed splinter cells in such woods as [[High Forest]], [[Cormanthor]], the [[Wealdath]], and the [[Great Dale]]. Despite the cells' humble sizes, they remained vigilant, keeping watch for foes such as the [[Church of Talos]] and the [[People of the Black Blood]]. Older established cells included those in the [[Chondalwood]] and [[Winterwood]].

Notable Members.Other Circles:
* [[Delaan Winterhound]], a chief ranger of the Emerald Enclave and its main delegate at the [[Council of Waterdeep]] in the late 15{{th}} century DR.
* [[Haarn Brightoak]], a druid tasked with protection of Turmishite land in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
* [[Screaming Wind]], a [[tabaxi]] hunter active in [[Chult]] in the late 15{{th}} century DR.{{Cite adventurers league/A City on the Edge|3}}
* [[Tick Tary Tanner]], Archmage of the [[High Forest]] in the late 15{{th}} century DR.<ref>{{Cite adventurers league/The Red War}}
